1
00:00:08,650 --> 00:00:11,010
<i>A sky blue champagne.</i>

2
00:00:14,970 --> 00:00:16,710
<i>The color of tears.</i>

3
00:00:17,950 --> 00:00:24,120
I'm so blessed to have met someone like you.

4
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:33,450
<i>A hue that perfectly expressed Sayaka.</i>

5
00:00:43,440 --> 00:00:45,620
<i>My days with Sayaka...</i>

6
00:00:46,240 --> 00:00:48,160
<i>were filled with nothing but happiness.</i>

7
00:00:49,330 --> 00:00:51,070
<i>Or so, they were supposed to be.</i>

8
00:01:01,190 --> 00:01:04,530
<i>I vowed to protect her.</i>

9
00:01:10,930 --> 00:01:17,290
<i>How can I be sure there's no ill intent
behind his "good intentions"?</i>

10
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:31,180
<i>An event to disrupt
the picture-perfect wedding.</i>

11
00:01:31,180 --> 00:01:32,460
- Sayaka!
- Sayaka!

12
00:01:32,460 --> 00:01:35,940
<i>The suspects who could have
orchestrated this hell...</i>

13
00:01:35,940 --> 00:01:37,680
I have my circumstances.

14
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:40,670
<i>are the groom, Kazuomi Hayashida...</i>

15
00:01:40,670 --> 00:01:43,810
<i>the bride's mother, Kaori Wakamatsu...</i>

16
00:01:43,810 --> 00:01:47,290
<i>the bride's friend, Chie Hashimoto...</i>

17
00:01:47,290 --> 00:01:49,510
<i>And...</i>

18
00:01:49,510 --> 00:01:53,750
- <i>perhaps the most suspicious one of all...</i>
- This person.

19
00:01:53,750 --> 00:01:55,150
Airi?

20
00:01:55,150 --> 00:01:58,240
There's something I can't overlook here.

21
00:01:58,240 --> 00:02:00,340
[SS-studio]

22
00:02:18,410 --> 00:02:21,730
I know you're in there.

23
00:02:26,290 --> 00:02:28,360
I'll be back.

24
00:02:37,940 --> 00:02:41,020
Was that a client?

25
00:02:42,190 --> 00:02:46,060
I remember seeing her at your exhibition.

26
00:02:47,860 --> 00:02:50,380
Don't tell me she's a stalker?

27
00:02:50,380 --> 00:02:54,000
I hear it's a real issue for younger artists.

28
00:02:54,780 --> 00:02:57,330
If you're in trouble, I'll help, alright?

29
00:02:57,330 --> 00:03:00,620
It's none of your business, Hayashida.

30
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:10,630
I adjusted the colors of that photo
sent with the threat.

31
00:03:10,630 --> 00:03:14,070
It should help a bit with readability.

32
00:03:14,850 --> 00:03:18,290
On the left... this is...

33
00:03:18,290 --> 00:03:21,070
Most likely Sayaka, right?

34
00:03:21,740 --> 00:03:23,670
Yeah, you're right.

35
00:03:24,890 --> 00:03:28,200
It's definitely Sayaka.

36
00:03:29,740 --> 00:03:37,060
What's this on the right, a rock?
Maybe a trash bag...

37
00:03:37,950 --> 00:03:39,940
Can't you make it any clearer?

38
00:03:39,940 --> 00:03:41,980
No can do.

39
00:03:41,980 --> 00:03:45,670
The original photo was blurry to begin with.

40
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:50,740
It's like they took it this way on purpose.

41
00:03:50,740 --> 00:03:54,070
You make a fair point.

42
00:03:55,290 --> 00:03:59,400
Is Sayaka wearing a sailor uniform here?

43
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:03,370
Looks like it.

44
00:04:03,370 --> 00:04:05,690
I get it now.

45
00:04:05,690 --> 00:04:09,060
That's why you suspect Airi,
her friend from school.

46
00:04:09,060 --> 00:04:12,620
This alone isn't incriminating evidence.

47
00:04:12,620 --> 00:04:15,840
- Hey, quit it -
- You're amazing, Sakuraba!

48
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:22,030
Alright, now I'm certain.

49
00:04:22,030 --> 00:04:27,380
The individual who sent this photo
has a clear grudge against Sayaka.

50
00:04:27,380 --> 00:04:34,410
And the sender, Airi Ozaki,
also poisoned her drink.

51
00:04:34,410 --> 00:04:37,800
What I wanted to talk about
were these reviews.

52
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:39,230
[Tastes fine,
but the worker's attitude is awful]

53
00:04:39,230 --> 00:04:41,940
Here, look.

54
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:48,480
This is the patisserie Sayaka worked at.

55
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:56,490
Airi looks especially photogenic here.

56
00:04:56,490 --> 00:04:58,610
She obviously edited the picture.

57
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:06,330
Take a look at this.

58
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:09,850
[Tastes fine,
but the worker's attitude is awful]

59
00:05:09,850 --> 00:05:11,170
[Tastes fine,
but the worker's attitude is awful]

60
00:05:11,170 --> 00:05:13,030
Haven't you noticed anything?

61
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:22,070
[airi_Oz - Posts]
[June 21st, 2025]

62
00:05:22,070 --> 00:05:24,820
[June 21st, 2025]

63
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:27,680
Seriously?

64
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:30,190
This time, I'm coming with you.

65
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:35,900
You're not getting anything done alone.

66
00:05:38,260 --> 00:05:45,950
I just want to solve the mystery,
and get back to my routine life.

67
00:05:47,470 --> 00:05:48,980
Thanks.

68
00:05:50,110 --> 00:05:55,610
Alright! We'll uncover Airi Ozaki's evil deeds.

69
00:05:57,160 --> 00:05:59,030
Sachiko!

70
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:05,930
<i>Is he searching for the culprit
for his beloved wife?</i>

71
00:06:05,930 --> 00:06:12,040
<i>Or to remove himself
from the list of suspects?</i>

72
00:06:18,630 --> 00:06:21,730
We've got a tailgater behind us.

73
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:27,860
They think their flashy car is so great.

74
00:06:27,860 --> 00:06:30,390
Maybe they really need to go.

75
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:33,440
Number one or number two...

76
00:06:33,440 --> 00:06:35,470
What do you think?

77
00:06:37,140 --> 00:06:40,460
You've got a vivid imagination.

78
00:06:40,460 --> 00:06:44,120
I drive a used, compact car.

79
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:47,110
I deal with tailgaters all the time.

80
00:06:47,110 --> 00:06:54,440
I plan to buy something better
when I get rich.

81
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:57,070
What's a photographer's annual salary?

82
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:03,310
Ever heard of "tact", Hayashida?

83
00:07:03,310 --> 00:07:07,030
I was just asking.
You said you wanted a nice car.

84
00:07:09,650 --> 00:07:14,040
I make less than 4 million yen a year.

85
00:07:15,780 --> 00:07:20,430
Though I work solely as
a commercial photographer now,

86
00:07:20,430 --> 00:07:25,040
I eventually want to branch out,
and treat my work as art.

87
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:28,500
Do you know Helmut Newton?

88
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:31,150
He's a role model of mine.

89
00:07:31,150 --> 00:07:38,490
I always thought it would be nice
to take such charged shots like his.

90
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:44,790
I just haven't found a subject
who particularly inspires me.

91
00:07:45,340 --> 00:07:49,090
I can't turn down commercial work
because I need the money.

92
00:07:49,090 --> 00:07:54,480
But if I only shoot for others,
I'll lose my personal touch.

93
00:07:56,370 --> 00:08:02,810
Didn't realize I was driving
with a famous photographer in the making.

94
00:08:02,810 --> 00:08:06,370
You're putting a damper on my spirits.

95
00:08:16,890 --> 00:08:20,810
I never had any dreams like you, Sakuraba.

96
00:08:20,810 --> 00:08:22,330
So I admire your drive.

97
00:08:22,330 --> 00:08:25,680
Sayaka's, too.

98
00:08:28,520 --> 00:08:32,350
Sayaka hoped to become a violinist, right?

99
00:08:32,350 --> 00:08:36,940
She practiced every day
instead of messing around like other kids.

100
00:08:36,940 --> 00:08:40,450
I imagine she was serious about it.

101
00:08:40,450 --> 00:08:45,610
Did she offer to play
at the ceremony herself?

102
00:08:45,610 --> 00:08:50,870
No, that was her mother's request.

103
00:08:56,770 --> 00:09:03,460
I wonder if Sayaka
really wanted to become a violinist.

104
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,850
What?

105
00:09:09,430 --> 00:09:11,410
[Limited Edition Strawberry Smoothie]

106
00:09:17,830 --> 00:09:19,440
Airi.

107
00:09:20,820 --> 00:09:22,790
Airi?

108
00:09:22,790 --> 00:09:24,060
Kazuomi.

109
00:09:24,060 --> 00:09:25,280
Hey there.

110
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:27,410
Thank you for making time for us.

111
00:09:27,410 --> 00:09:29,340
Of course. I'm sorry it had to be a weekday.

112
00:09:29,340 --> 00:09:34,640
No worries. This is Sakuraba,
who I mentioned over the phone.

113
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:38,400
He would appreciate your advice
as a tax counselor.

114
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:40,060
Isn't that right?

115
00:09:40,060 --> 00:09:43,060
You used me as an excuse.

116
00:09:43,060 --> 00:09:44,960
"Excuse"?

117
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:47,970
- Shall we head on in?
- Right.

118
00:09:54,920 --> 00:09:57,210
- Your coffees.
- Thank you.

119
00:09:59,940 --> 00:10:02,400
Here you go.

120
00:10:02,910 --> 00:10:05,320
Sorry, were you not a coffee drinker?

121
00:10:05,320 --> 00:10:07,000
No, coffee's fine.

122
00:10:16,930 --> 00:10:21,760
My sincere condolences
for the wedding, and Sayaka.

123
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:28,000
I appreciate the introduction to a client,
but please understand if I seem out of it.

124
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,400
Airi.

125
00:10:29,990 --> 00:10:34,680
We didn't call you here today
to discuss taxes.

126
00:10:35,620 --> 00:10:40,590
We came to ask about your negative reviews
written about Sayaka.

127
00:10:46,710 --> 00:10:52,180
"The employee here is incompetent.
She's slow, and practically inaudible."

128
00:10:52,180 --> 00:10:53,140
"I question her work ethic."

129
00:10:53,140 --> 00:10:54,960
I'm sorry, what?

130
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:58,670
You wrote these reviews, did you not?

131
00:10:58,670 --> 00:11:00,820
No, of course not.

132
00:11:00,820 --> 00:11:02,570
You're not fooling us.

133
00:11:02,570 --> 00:11:06,120
I cherish Sayaka.

134
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:08,890
I would never slander her. She's my -

135
00:11:08,890 --> 00:11:11,960
"Dear friend"?

136
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,690
That's right.

137
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:18,220
I've been there for her,
ever since we were in high school.

138
00:11:25,380 --> 00:11:27,000
Y-You're...

139
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:31,160
I can't believe you would resort
to such lies and cheap tricks.

140
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:33,010
I'm leaving.

141
00:11:33,010 --> 00:11:38,970
So this is what people look like
when they snap back.

142
00:11:38,970 --> 00:11:40,470
What?

143
00:11:42,980 --> 00:11:45,290
This is a photo from your account.

144
00:11:45,290 --> 00:11:51,470
It was uploaded the same day
this review was posted.

145
00:11:56,390 --> 00:11:57,250
[June 7th, 2025]

146
00:11:57,250 --> 00:12:01,720
The date and location are exactly the same.

147
00:12:02,310 --> 00:12:04,780
It's a coincidence.

148
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:06,960
It happens multiple times.

149
00:12:08,770 --> 00:12:11,090
Here's another "coincidence".

150
00:12:11,090 --> 00:12:17,470
Same date, and location as each review.

151
00:12:17,470 --> 00:12:18,940
Only the reviewers themselves differ.

152
00:12:18,940 --> 00:12:21,550
You must have several burner accounts.

153
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:24,350
All to bash on Sayaka's work.

154
00:12:24,350 --> 00:12:29,110
I'm impressed you can keep track
of so many personas.

155
00:12:29,110 --> 00:12:31,860
I told you, I had no hand in this.

156
00:12:37,260 --> 00:12:43,760
These reviews die down from November to May.

157
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:49,190
Tax firms get busy around that time.

158
00:12:53,020 --> 00:12:54,850
Ozaki.

159
00:12:54,850 --> 00:12:59,590
Are you familiar with the concept
of disclosing personal information?

160
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:04,890
These reviews are clearly aimed at Sayaka.

161
00:13:04,890 --> 00:13:08,400
They would be filed as excessive harassment.

162
00:13:09,010 --> 00:13:15,510
I plan on introducing Hayashida to a lawyer
who excels in this sort of case.

163
00:13:15,510 --> 00:13:18,490
A lawyer, for something like this?

164
00:13:18,490 --> 00:13:20,250
But of course.

165
00:13:20,250 --> 00:13:25,650
You insist you're innocent,
so what else can we do?

166
00:13:29,150 --> 00:13:32,430
We'd want to settle this peacefully,
for Sayaka's sake.

167
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:37,680
But if the culprit won't budge...

168
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:44,010
then we'll have to bring this to court.

169
00:14:05,490 --> 00:14:07,800
Guilty as charged.

170
00:14:35,190 --> 00:14:37,290
Yes, I wrote those reviews.

171
00:14:37,290 --> 00:14:40,400
But it was all for Sayaka.

172
00:14:43,010 --> 00:14:45,600
Two canelé, coming right up.

173
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:46,500
T-To go?

174
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:49,940
<i>The employee here is incompetent.</i>

175
00:14:49,940 --> 00:14:55,290
<i>She's slow, and practically inaudible.</i>

176
00:14:55,290 --> 00:14:57,250
<i>I question her work ethic.</i>

177
00:14:59,640 --> 00:15:02,010
No, not that one.

178
00:15:02,010 --> 00:15:07,070
<i>I was only telling her
she grabbed the wrong cake.</i>

179
00:15:11,670 --> 00:15:13,180
I'm so sorry.

180
00:15:13,180 --> 00:15:17,420
<i>But then she began crying,
and conversing became impossible.</i>

181
00:15:17,420 --> 00:15:20,040
<i>She made me feel like the bad guy.</i>

182
00:15:20,040 --> 00:15:21,410
I'm so sorry, sir.

183
00:15:21,410 --> 00:15:24,830
<i>These cakes taste great,
but I won't be coming again.</i>

184
00:15:24,830 --> 00:15:30,160
If she doesn't fix her work ethic,
she really ought to quit.

185
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:31,190
You're lying.

186
00:15:31,190 --> 00:15:32,100
"Lying"?

187
00:15:32,100 --> 00:15:35,510
You're making biased accusations against her.

188
00:15:35,510 --> 00:15:37,530
I never lied.

189
00:15:37,530 --> 00:15:39,100
I only wrote the truth.

190
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:40,710
Sayaka was doing her best.

191
00:15:40,710 --> 00:15:43,520
But she wasn't doing enough.

192
00:15:43,520 --> 00:15:48,250
A seasoned worker like her
ought to do her job well.

193
00:15:48,250 --> 00:15:52,320
And crying in front of a customer?
That's no way for an adult to act.

194
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:55,640
Kind words won't change her attitude.

195
00:15:55,640 --> 00:15:58,450
Let alone advice from a friend.

196
00:15:58,450 --> 00:16:02,040
So I thought to advise her in other ways.

197
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:08,150
Sayaka needed critique from a third party
to see her own shortcomings.

198
00:16:08,150 --> 00:16:09,640
You were so cruel to her.

199
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:12,460
Don't be so quick to call it cruelty.

200
00:16:12,460 --> 00:16:16,870
I wrote those reviews for Sayaka's sake.

201
00:16:16,870 --> 00:16:18,330
Airi.

202
00:16:20,180 --> 00:16:25,080
Do you feel no shame in what you've done?

203
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:28,590
Ultimately, this is an issue
of Sayaka's mental state.

204
00:16:28,590 --> 00:16:33,490
If you think these reviews
are what sent Sayaka to a therapist,

205
00:16:33,490 --> 00:16:35,090
then you're wrong.

206
00:16:35,090 --> 00:16:40,690
Sayaka always went crying to a doctor
whenever something went wrong.

207
00:16:40,690 --> 00:16:46,200
Though given how Sayaka's mother is,
I'm sure it stemmed from issues at home.

208
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:53,600
I only wanted to strengthen
her fragile mentality.

209
00:16:53,600 --> 00:17:00,000
But Sayaka lost her chance to change
because she began seeing you.

210
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:05,090
You're too soft on her, Kazuomi.

211
00:17:05,090 --> 00:17:07,880
Your constant sympathy is of no help to her.

212
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:10,090
Sayaka needs someone to protect her.

213
00:17:10,090 --> 00:17:12,640
She can't just cling to men all her life.

214
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:15,770
This is exactly why she's never changed.

215
00:17:15,770 --> 00:17:19,780
It's about time she learns
to become independent.

216
00:17:22,510 --> 00:17:26,490
I take it you know
Sayaka worked at a ConCafe.

217
00:17:26,490 --> 00:17:32,270
Did you know she had relationships
with several of her customers?

218
00:17:32,270 --> 00:17:37,490
She sought out solace in dating apps as well.

219
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:41,280
Excuse me.

220
00:17:42,530 --> 00:17:45,040
This is a bit much. He's Sayaka's husband.

221
00:17:46,650 --> 00:17:49,250
I'm informing him because he's her husband.

222
00:17:59,230 --> 00:18:01,090
Don't act like you have good intentions.

223
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:18,390
You send us a threat,
and say it's all for Sayaka?

224
00:18:18,390 --> 00:18:19,680
I've had enough.

225
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:21,640
Is this why you poisoned Sayaka?

226
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:24,650
Poison? What poison?

227
00:18:24,650 --> 00:18:26,790
Is that why Sayaka collapsed?

228
00:18:26,790 --> 00:18:28,970
You won't fool us twice.

229
00:18:30,850 --> 00:18:35,510
This isn't our high school uniform.

230
00:18:35,510 --> 00:18:38,330
If you recall the picture from earlier...

231
00:18:40,050 --> 00:18:43,820
See, look. Our uniform was a blazer.

232
00:18:43,820 --> 00:18:46,240
I didn't know Sayaka before high school.

233
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:51,800
Neither did Chie.
We wouldn't have a photo like this.

234
00:18:54,390 --> 00:18:59,680
I'm sure you must pity "poor Sayaka".

235
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:03,450
But that's not love. It's nothing at all.

236
00:19:03,450 --> 00:19:06,900
You're only looking down on her.

237
00:19:06,900 --> 00:19:07,770
How dare you...

238
00:19:07,770 --> 00:19:11,930
I am Sayaka's best friend.
I would never poison her.

239
00:19:11,930 --> 00:19:17,870
I only corrected her weaknesses,
from a place of love.

240
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:22,800
Everything I've done, is for Sayaka's sake.

241
00:19:38,530 --> 00:19:40,520
What a woman.

242
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:46,310
Airi Ozaki looked nothing like herself
from high school.

243
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:49,390
They were practically different individuals.

244
00:19:51,460 --> 00:19:54,810
I'd reckon she got plastic surgery.

245
00:19:59,360 --> 00:20:00,990
Plastic surgery?

246
00:20:01,750 --> 00:20:08,650
She likely craves superiority,
in all aspects of her life.

247
00:20:09,630 --> 00:20:11,660
Why?

248
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:15,830
She most likely has a complex of sorts.

249
00:20:16,710 --> 00:20:20,060
<i>With her twisted sense of justice,</i>

250
00:20:20,060 --> 00:20:25,010
<i>Airi Ozaki sends Sayaka
into the depths of despair.</i>

251
00:20:25,010 --> 00:20:28,230
<i>What a fantastic friendship indeed.</i>

252
00:20:29,150 --> 00:20:32,260
I thought she was a friend of Sayaka.

253
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:36,170
I thought she was a good person.

254
00:20:36,170 --> 00:20:39,000
To think she'd be such a villain.

255
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:42,060
A villain, huh?

256
00:20:42,060 --> 00:20:47,600
<i>Those with good intent often look down on
the very people they're helping.</i>

257
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:51,560
<i>But Airi Ozaki won't ever see her faults.</i>

258
00:20:51,560 --> 00:20:54,820
<i>Because she never had ill intentions.</i>

259
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:02,980
I was sure she was the culprit.

260
00:21:03,710 --> 00:21:05,930
I suppose we were off the mark.

261
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:10,920
It wasn't Chie.

262
00:21:12,780 --> 00:21:15,060
And it wasn't Airi Ozaki, either.

263
00:21:17,900 --> 00:21:20,060
Which only leaves one individual.

264
00:21:34,120 --> 00:21:39,440
<i>The only suspect left is Sayaka's mother,
Kaori Wakamatsu.</i>

265
00:21:41,220 --> 00:21:47,180
<i>But what if Kazuomi Hayashida</i>

266
00:21:47,180 --> 00:21:52,490
<i>knew everything of his wife's past?</i>

267
00:22:05,490 --> 00:22:07,670
[Kazuomi Hayashida]

268
00:22:15,190 --> 00:22:16,840
<i>I take it you know
Sayaka worked at a ConCafe.</i>

269
00:22:16,840 --> 00:22:19,070
<i>She had relationships
with several of her customers.</i>

270
00:22:19,070 --> 00:22:22,080
<i>She sought out solace in dating apps as well.</i>

271
00:22:51,820 --> 00:22:53,480
Sayaka.
